publication.name: Kaplan vs. Kaplan

quote: Despite Phoenix's riveting performance, I cannot recommend this movie.
critic.name: David Kaplan
publication.name: Kaplan vs. Kaplan

quote: The movie doesn't make excuses; it simply lays out this life in decline and dares us to watch how it turns out.
critic.name: Steven Prokopy
publication.name: Third Coast Review

quote: Joker is an exploration of what causes a lonely, unhinged man to explode, and it has moments that are riveting.
critic.name: Moira MacDonald
publication.name: Seattle Times

quote: From a conceptual standpoint, Joker certainly had the pieces to be a phenomenal film, but this did not need to be in the hands of Todd Phillips.
critic.name: Rendy Jones
publication.name: Rendy Reviews

quote: Phoenix makes his mark as a severely damaged man who becomes an insane monster, a maestro of madness who sinks to the bottom of society but moves to the top of the DC Villains Hall of Fame.
critic.name: Neil Pond
publication.name: Parade Magazine

quote: Joker has what may be the best lead performance of the year, but it is not for the faint of heart. Director Todd Phillips digs deep into the shadow side of society for one of the darkest movies in recent memory.
critic.name: Karen Gordon
publication.name: Original Cin

quote: The year's biggest disappointment has arrived.
critic.name: Peter Bradshaw
publication.name: Guardian

quote: As stuffed as the fat cats are meant to be, however, the cinematic manor in which they here reside is really just an empty shell that thinks it's full.
critic.name: Christopher Llewellyn Reed
publication.name: Film Festival Today

quote: The sum of Joker's glib philosophy seems to be that there's a lot of dark stuff out there, and that should really make you think.
critic.name: Ian Mantgani
publication.name: The Skinny

quote: Joker is an ambitious film, and though it just can't quite match the performances with technical prowess, it makes up for it with a compelling character study and some lofty themes.
critic.name: Michelle Kisner
publication.name: The Movie Sleuth

quote: A towering performance from Phoenix, who becomes the best to ever do it ('it' being the ultimate acting challenge of depicting the clown who fights Batman).
critic.name: Simon Miraudo
publication.name: Student Edge

quote: In an era where almost all films look the same, sound the same, and taste same thing, few filmmakers dare to do something like Joker, much less big studios. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Jorge Rivera Rubio
publication.name: QiiBO

quote: Joaquin's poisonous performance is maniacally mesmerizing.
critic.name: Don Shanahan
publication.name: Every Movie Has a Lesson

quote: Phillips has a big idea for "Joker," but he doesn't make much of a movie with it, with the possibilities of the feature more enticing than the realities of it.
critic.name: Brian Orndorf
publication.name: Blu-ray.com

quote: Joker wasn't for me, and even if I were to dance with the devil in the pale moonlight and have a sudden desire to see the world burn that still doesn't mean I see my opinion changing anytime soon.
critic.name: Sara Michelle Fetters
publication.name: MovieFreak.com

quote: The "Joker" America deserves, and craves, in this dark hour.
critic.name: Roger Moore
publication.name: Movie Nation

quote: Joker is basically an idiot's version of a thinking man's film.
critic.name: Kyle Pinion
publication.name: Screen Rex

quote: A shallow movie playing at being deep, a basic movie that thinks it's complex, not even particularly shocking or violent or transgressive enough to be "outraged" about in any meaningful way. It has nothing much to say - and yet it won't shut up.
critic.name: Bob Chipman
publication.name: Escapist Magazine

quote: It is impossible to remain untouched by his grief. Entertainment is not what this film is offering, but phenomenal acting, excellent technical filmmaking, and awareness of the empathy we lack as human beings.
critic.name: Sucharita Tyagi
publication.name: Film Companion

quote: ...the problem with "Joker" is the lack of a proper foil.
critic.name: Jonathan W. Hickman
publication.name: Daily Film Fix

quote: Phillips' Joker doesn't have the depth or clarity of vision to match up to its star's performance.
critic.name: Josh Bell
publication.name: CBR

quote: [Todd] Phillips finds no throughline but hate, his disdain popping from the relentless grime of Gotham City like Joker's garish purple suit.
critic.name: Dom Sinacola
publication.name: Paste Magazine

quote: Here's a killing joke: director Todd Phillips doesn't understand why his own origin story/character study of Joker is a masterpiece
critic.name: Robert Kojder
publication.name: Flickering Myth

quote: It's as if Phillips had a burning desire to create his own version of Taxi Driver, but wasn't sure audiences would show up, so he slapped a coat of green hair dye and greasepaint onto the screenplay to guarantee plenty of asses in seats.
critic.name: Brent Hankins
publication.name: The Lamplight Review

quote: 'Joker' is a film that is simply trying to elicit a response and provoke viewers. It is not what you will be expecting from a big-budget movie with a DC logo slapped on it. How Phillips made something that is on par with 'Taxi Driver' is utterly shocking.
critic.name: Preston Barta
publication.name: Denton Record-Chronicle

quote: If there's any danger related to Joker, that would be a result not of a supposedly "incel" apology (which it's not), but of how attractive it makes nihilism look. [Full review in Portuguese]
critic.name: Pablo Villaça
publication.name: Cinema em Cena

quote: With Oscar worthy performances, most notably by Joaquin Phoneix, as well as Lawrence Sher's beautiful cinematography and composer Hildur Guðnadóttir's haunting score, the film packs a wallop of a punch to all senses.
critic.name: Shannon McGrew
publication.name: Nightmarish Conjurings

quote: Although it may be difficult to "like" this film in a conventional sense, it offers a powerful and unforgettable experience that few will find easy to shake.
critic.name: James Berardinelli
publication.name: ReelViews

quote: Phoenix and Phillips turn Joker into a sociopolitical mishmash.
critic.name: Armond White
publication.name: National Review

quote: Todd Phillips and Joaquin Phoenix successfully make a compelling comic book movie which focuses on character over spectacle.
critic.name: Sean Chandler
publication.name: Sean Chandler Talks About

quote: an uncomfortable, accusatory character study, as it catches us on one side or another of Fleck's misplaced laughter, and tries to get us all to dance to his bloody steps.
critic.name: Anton Bitel
publication.name: Projected Figures

quote: Forget escapism. Joker rubs our faces in angst, yet it is brilliant in its ugliness.
critic.name: Robert W. Butler
publication.name: Butler's Cinema Scene

quote: Joaquin Phoenix as Joker will haunt the recesses of my soul until the end of time.
critic.name: Kate Rodger
publication.name: Newshub (NZ)

quote: It's a film about cinema, made by and for pop culture sophisticates. It doesn't have to mean anything.
critic.name: Kerry Lengel
publication.name: Arizona Republic

quote: "Joker" is resoundingly one-note throughout the majority of its running time, Phillips mistaking "unrelentingly grim" for "profound," which just renders the film punishingly dull.
critic.name: Katie Walsh
publication.name: Tribune News Service

quote: It's not too much to ask -- and more than just being a scold -- for justification of an exercise that places such a villain front and center, especially when there is so little light or goodness to balance the darkness.
critic.name: Brian Lowry
publication.name: CNN.com

quote: the film's main asset is Phoenix's insane tour de force, the actor projecting a tortured physique, his torso twisted and ribs projecting as he moves with a grace that can only be called balletic.
critic.name: Laura Clifford
publication.name: Reeling Reviews

quote: Joaquin Phoenix is next level amazing in "Joker," and this is definitely the movie Todd Phillips set out to make, but I'm not sure it's one that should have been made.
critic.name: Joey Magidson
publication.name: Hollywood News

quote: Not fit to lick the boots of Martin Scorsese or Christopher Nolan, though the height of its ambition appears to be its desperation to do so. A movie as pathetically ineffectual as its protagonist.
critic.name: MaryAnn Johanson
publication.name: Flick Filosopher

quote: With Phoenix appearing in virtually every minute of this movie and dominating the screen with his memorably creepy turn, "Joker" will cling to you like the aftermath of an unfortunately realistic nightmare.
critic.name: Richard Roeper
publication.name: Chicago Sun-Times

quote: In a year of mass culture that gave us HBO's excellent "Chernobyl," "Joker" can claim the grimmest depiction of a meltdown.
critic.name: Michael Phillips
publication.name: Chicago Tribune

quote: Having unleashed Phoenix, Phillips doesn't seem to know how to contain or couch the performance. At some point he seems to have surrendered, and when the movie is over you realize Arthur is its only substantial character.
critic.name: Gary Thompson
publication.name: Philadelphia Daily News

quote: A ghastly-good Phoenix can't save this slice of faux social commentary.
critic.name: Rafer Guzman
publication.name: Newsday

quote: As unsettling as it is rapturous. Sobering and, yes, shocking, "Joker" creatively invigorates in its sheer unvarnished madness.
critic.name: Dustin Putman
publication.name: TheFilmFile.com

quote: It is a narcissistic fantasy beloved of mass shooters and war criminals, not antiheroes.
critic.name: John Lui
publication.name: The Straits Times (Singapore)

quote: Todd Phillips' take on the iconic Batman nemesis has a lot on its mind. Too bad it blasts it all so relentlessly almost none of it leaves a lasting mark.
critic.name: Joanna Langfield
publication.name: The Movie Minute

quote: Joker isn't the film to seriously tackle the issue[s]--it's more concerned with flair than genuine inquiry--but Phoenix's pained, raw-nerve performance is one for the ages.
critic.name: Peter Canavese
publication.name: Groucho Reviews

quote: It's kind of amazing such an empty spectacle has sparked so much heated debate, but then, comic book movies usually are over-hyped.
critic.name: Sarah Marrs
publication.name: Lainey Gossip

quote: Phoenix gives the role a frightening intensity. This actor doesn't favour dilettante distancing. He steps right through the looking glass to become the character he has been staring at.
critic.name: Nigel Andrews
publication.name: Financial Times

quote: Phoenix is brilliant at exploring the depths of his demise to his ascent to avenging angel gone horribly wrong. He punctuates every step with sneering laughter.
critic.name: John Petkovic
publication.name: Cleveland Plain Dealer

quote: It is made well, but overall, it's a childish, meandering story that didn't deserve the attention it got, but also doesn't deserve much other than acting praise.
critic.name: Princess Weekes
publication.name: The Mary Sue

quote: [Joaquin Phoenix] never manages to make Arthur into a coherent person, partly because it's hard to see this schmuck as any kind of future arch-villain and partly because the film's thesis is kept broad and vague.
critic.name: Jake Wilson
publication.name: The Age (Australia)

quote: Phoenix delivers a mesmerizing performance and catapults into one of the best interpretations of Batman's most famous archenemy and an equally Oscar-worthy performance.
critic.name: Jazz Tangcay
publication.name: AwardsWatch

quote: As a piece of art, and film is an art form, Joker masterfully finds a voice for the brutal and believable backstory for The Joker. In the end, however, this is a film for super hero fans.
critic.name: Pamela Powell
publication.name: Reel Honest Reviews

quote: You're probably going to leave the film feeling uncomfortable, but you'll also be wowed by Phoenix's performance. He's gunning for an Oscar nod as the Clown Prince of Crime and he may certainly get it.
critic.name: Kirsten Acuna
publication.name: Insider

quote: Phoenix is truly outstanding in a performance which almost seems like an extension of his role in Lynne Ramsay's stunning 2017 crime thriller You Were Never Really Here.
critic.name: Linda Marric
publication.name: The Jewish Chronicle

quote: Joker assesses society's fraught structure, the cyclical nature of violence, the damage we allow to be passed onto those less fortunate and more at-risk, and treats it to a punchline. And that's okay. Why so serious?
critic.name: Matt Oakes
publication.name: Silver Screen Riot

quote: Joker plays like the Clown Prince's own propaganda film, a flimsy, sloppy "You Made Me Do This" ex post facto justification for all the criminal havoc he wreaks on Gotham in the ensuing years.
critic.name: Andrew Wyatt
publication.name: The Lens

quote: Consciously channelling classics such as Taxi Driver and The King Of Comedy, it's a visually striking, breathtakingly dangerous reflection of our broken times wherein a deluded loner finally finds himself empowered and noticed when he picks up a gun.
critic.name: Larushka Ivan-Zadeh
publication.name: Metro Newspaper (UK)

quote: As a long form explanation why some dudes can literally get away with murder, Joker is a massive success/instructional video.
critic.name: Jeffrey Lyles
publication.name: Lyles' Movie Files

quote: In the end, we hope that Joker is the spearhead for new ways to adapt the comics to the big screen. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Abigail Camarillo
publication.name: Chilango.com

quote: Even if we ignore the immaturity and shallowness of its messaging, there's a lot of mess in Joker that not even watching Phoenix do his thing for two hours can fully shake.
critic.name: Clint Worthington
publication.name: The Spool

quote: As Joker gets grimmer and descends further into bloody violence, it becomes little more than a horror show, bludgeoning its viewers out of any chance at insight.
critic.name: David Sims
publication.name: The Atlantic

quote: I was riveted by this movie from just about start to finish.
critic.name: Chris Stuckmann
publication.name: ChrisStuckmann.com

quote: The last laugh of someone who simply wants to watch the world burn.
critic.name: Matthew Razak
publication.name: Flixist.com

quote: Joaquin Phoenix goes full Clown Prince of Crime in Phillips' stylish crime drama, but it's not enough to mask the sense of emptiness at Joker's core.
critic.name: Sandy Schaefer
publication.name: Screen Rant

quote: Todd Phillips clearly understands the plots of the Scorsese movies he's copied, but not their souls.
critic.name: Matt Singer
publication.name: ScreenCrush

quote: After all the speculation, adulation, and accusations paving the way for me on the way to seeing Joker, the final product is compelling enough, without becoming something grander.
critic.name: Aaron Neuwirth
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: [Joaquin Phoenix] thrives under the weight and pressure of portraying the most iconic comic book villain of all time.
critic.name: Jeremy Jahns
publication.name: JeremyJahns.com

quote: Headlined by Joaquin Phoenix's spellbinding performance, Joker is uncomfortable, visceral and raw; setting a new standard of quality for all comic book-based films.
critic.name: Sheraz Farooqi
publication.name: CinemaDebate

quote: It's provocative, disturbing, occasionally funny, sometimes heartbreaking and the way Phillips plays with the intensity dial is incredible.
critic.name: Simon Gallagher
publication.name: What Culture

quote: Joker is a cautionary tale. It's saying, 'Don't create Jokers. They won't just go away if you ignore them.'
critic.name: Fred Topel
publication.name: Showbiz Cheat Sheet

quote: BRILLIANT. Joker goes too far, but intentionally so. For all the talk of "inciting violence", it's shocking that nobody is talking about this film's OTHER important messages.
critic.name: Grace Randolph
publication.name: Beyond the Trailer

quote: I find it ridiculous that the same people who reject the notion of movies being responsible for inciting real-life violence are the ones panicking about Joker inspiring mass shooters.
critic.name: Rohan Naahar
publication.name: Hindustan Times

quote: Phillips has created a compelling character study with Phoenix's performance something that will be talked about for a long time.
critic.name: Edward Douglas
publication.name: The Weekend Warrior

quote: Gritty and grubby, garish and loud, violent and depressing, Joker is a blunt instrument of a movie - though it is a good movie. Phoenix is superb, Arthur Fleck's downward spiral inverted into an ascent to antihero status as Gotham seethes then explodes.
critic.name: Sarah Cartland
publication.name: Caution Spoilers

quote: This "Joker" doesn't care about the violence it perpetuates, but wants credit for pretending to care.
critic.name: Sean P. Means
publication.name: Salt Lake Tribune

quote: Like the anti-hero at its center, it's a movie trying so hard to be capital-b Big that it can't help looking small.
critic.name: Ann Hornaday
publication.name: Washington Post

quote: The Joker is deadly serious, a bleak but oddly beautiful horror film that evokes the nightmarish nihilism of Martin Scorsese's Taxi Driver.
critic.name: Paul Whitington
publication.name: Irish Independent

quote: A power and free film and almost improper of Hollywood in the times they are in. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Víctor López G.
publication.name: Espinof

quote: Starting as a powerfully unsettling character study, it builds to the kind of corny and obvious finale you'd expect from, yes, a studio superhero movie.
critic.name: Gavia Baker-Whitelaw
publication.name: The Daily Dot

quote: Yes, this is the story of the birth of a popular super villain, but "Joker" has much bigger issues on its mind.
critic.name: Adam Graham
publication.name: Detroit News

quote: I didn't hate the movie. Actually, I think it's kind of great in many ways, but the things it does badly are tough to ignore...Joker is good. Not great, but certainly not a world-ending disaster.
critic.name: Kayleigh Donaldson
publication.name: Syfy Wire

quote: It's interesting that Todd Phillips had to get so far away from the character to find the brightest way to put it on the screen. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Jonay Armas
publication.name: Caimán Cuadernos de Cine

quote: Joaquin Phoenix isn't so much an actor as a moral contortionist in this mesmerising origin story.
critic.name: Vicky Roach
publication.name: Daily Telegraph (Australia)

quote: Its themes will polarise audiences but there is no denying Philips' devastating reimagination of an iconic character. Along with Phoenix's staggering performance, this is one Joker that can be serious.
critic.name: Katie Smith-Wong
publication.name: Flick Feast

quote: The best film of 2019. If Phoenix doesn't take home an Oscar the villains will be sitting on the Academy.
critic.name: Andy Lea
publication.name: Daily Star (UK)

quote: Joker... is, like the character at the centre of it all, hard to define, but leaves an indelible impression.
critic.name: Andrew Parker
publication.name: The Gate

quote: Forget the overhyped controversy, Joker is simply stupendous as entertainment and provocation, with a gut-punch performance by Phoenix that puts a horrifically human face on an iconic comic-book villain.
critic.name: Peter Travers
publication.name: Rolling Stone

quote: Joker is bold and provocative in measures that make even the grittiest superhero tentpoles seem safe. Joaquin Phoenix is a revelation.
critic.name: Shaun Munro
publication.name: Flickering Myth

quote: A chilling masterpiece. Both disturbing and fascinating. Joaquin Phoenix is extraordinary. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Fico Cangiano
publication.name: CineXpress

quote: Disturbing and intense, yet undeniably brilliant, this may very well become the definitive origin tale of the Joker.
critic.name: Neil Soans
publication.name: The Times of India

quote: Origin stories are never going to be the same again...
critic.name: Devesh Sharma
publication.name: Filmfare

quote: If you want to watch a rejected loner with a history of trauma and a conflicted relationship with their mother make the world burn for how they were treated, try Carrie.
critic.name: Amanda Jane Robinson
publication.name: Flicks.co.nz

quote: We are here for a grim fairground ride and Joaquin Phoenix, whose title character kicks everything else into distant wings, spares no effort in keeping us diverted throughout.
critic.name: Donald Clarke
publication.name: Irish Times

quote: It's gorgeous to look at and splendidly acted, but it works much better as a singular character study than as a broader sociopolitical drama.
critic.name: Scott Mendelson
publication.name: Forbes

quote: "Joker" is on the surface the origin of a supervillain but more subtly an exploration of empathy and the personal impact of a society devoid of it.
critic.name: Brian Truitt
publication.name: USA Today

quote: Despite a strong performance from Joaquin Phoenix, Todd Phillips' Scorsese-infused adaptation is less than the sum of its parts.
critic.name: Matt Goldberg
publication.name: Collider

quote: Thanks to Joaquin Phoenix's Joker there is no excuse for not taking comics-inspired movies seriously. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Nando Salvá
publication.name: Cinemanía (Spain)

quote: Despite Phillips' questionable and unwatched filmography, I found myself on board with his Joker flick.
critic.name: Rosalie Kicks
publication.name: MovieJawn

quote: Phoenix's Joker fashions everything, all the pain and frustration, into a weapon, the tip of a spear that can rally others who are feeling the same.
critic.name: tt stern-enzi
publication.name: Cincinnati CityBeat

quote: The strenuous effort of Phoenix's performance that it becomes exhausting to behold. Get a load of me, he seems to say, and the load is almost too much to bear.
critic.name: Anthony Lane
publication.name: New Yorker

quote: Joker is intense and unnerving and a radical entry into the superhero genre, but come on, Taxi Driver was 40 years ago.
critic.name: Richard Trenholm
publication.name: CNET

quote: Regardless of where you will personally sit in reaction to its material, the fact it's inspiring conversation is an achievement in itself, and what [Todd] Phillips and particularly [Joaquin] Phoenix have created is nothing less than admirable.
critic.name: Peter Gray
publication.name: This is Film

quote: ...a stark commentary on the human condition.
critic.name: David Stratton
publication.name: The Australian

quote: The movie as a whole doesn't quite match up to the brilliance of Phoenix's powerhouse performance. Still, it's not far off: thrilling and unsettling in equal measure, Joker is a film that thrives on the edge -- and that's what makes it so compelling.
critic.name: Richard Jordan
publication.name: Den of Geek

quote: drags you kicking and screaming inside the worldview of a man as he goes violently insane
critic.name: Chris Hunneysett
publication.name: Daily Mirror (UK)

quote: There are films that push you to the limit, have you on the edge, and then there's Joker, starring the brilliance of Joaquin Phoenix.
critic.name: Min-sik Yoon
publication.name: Korea Herald

quote: It's a very good movie, and it features a blood-curdling performance from Joaquin Phoenix, in the most frightening portrayal of a violent maniac in decades.
critic.name: Mick LaSalle
publication.name: San Francisco Chronicle

quote: We are not given a genre-bending Joker film that taps into the fascinating anarchistic chaos and oddly enticing charisma of the character, we are instead given a sub-par remake of 'Taxi Driver' with the DC logo attached to it.
critic.name: Ciaran Kerr
publication.name: Film Bunker

quote: ...delivers one of the more haunting and unique comic book movie experiences in years.
critic.name: Anthony O'Connor
publication.name: FILMINK (Australia)

quote: It is Joaquin Phoenix as the Joker that really makes the film. Phoenix is weirdly brilliant from beginning to end, giving a performance which is by turns heartbreaking and frightening.
critic.name: Monica Reid
publication.name: Far Out Magazine

quote: See this film immediately.
critic.name: Jamie East
publication.name: The Sun (UK)

quote: You might not put on a happy face for a while after the credits roll, but it is so worth the weird dreams that will likely follow.
critic.name: Sinead Brennan
publication.name: RTÉ (Ireland)

quote: But for all the technical prowess on display and Phoenix's wonderful performance, Joker can't help feeling a bit shallow in other departments.
critic.name: Ian Sandwell
publication.name: Digital Spy

quote: Joker is a brazenly breathtaking film with Joaquin Phoenix delivering an out-of-this-world performance as the clown prince of crime and Todd Phillips soars with his utterly beautiful direction.
critic.name: Ben Rolph
publication.name: Discussing Film

quote: A joyless film with the wit and emotional intelligence of a school shooter manifesto.
critic.name: Jon Dieringer
publication.name: Screen Slate

quote: 'Joker' is buoyed almost entirely by Phoenix's performance - it really is that spectacular - and the boldness in how it tries to interpret one of the most recognisable characters in popular culture.
critic.name: Brian Lloyd
publication.name: entertainment.ie

quote: Edgy and darkly disturbing, Joker takes flight on the wings of a sensational performance by Joaquin Phoenix.
critic.name: Louise Keller
publication.name: Urban Cinefile

quote: Whether your first instinct is to revel in the performance or be repulsed by it is of no apparent consequence to writer-director Todd Phillips. No matter what you do, you're compelled to respond.
critic.name: David Crow
publication.name: Den of Geek

quote: A bold, layered, and unsettling cautionary tale that laughs at superhero-genre conventions to become one of the best films of the year. What Joaquin Phoenix does is pure cinematic alchemy. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Nestor Bentancor
publication.name: Nestor Cine Desde Hollywood

quote: The less I think about Joker as a comic book movie, the more I like it. Joaquin Phoenix is brilliant...Grim, gritty, harsh, and disturbing.
critic.name: Dan Murrell
publication.name: Screen Junkies

quote: Another actor will have to give a superhero-like performance to wrestle the 2020 Best Actor Oscar away from Phoenix.
critic.name: Jeff Mitchell
publication.name: Phoenix Film Festival

quote: Phillips directs a pretty entertaining film that is commanded by Phoenix's performance. His commitment to the role is Joker's most compelling aspect and he makes it his own through his physicality and delivery.
critic.name: Ricky Church
publication.name: Flickering Myth

quote: Joker desperately searches for something to make it distinctive - and it doesn't succeed.
critic.name: Joi Childs
publication.name: MTR Network

quote: The formula of the movie betrays us... it leaves us halfway to the demonstration of, as it is literally and figuratively said in the movie, "we are all clowns". [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Erick Estrada
publication.name: Cinegarage

quote: Joker is about a lunatic gaining infamy, sure. But this film is really about a movement. It's about what happens to people who fall through the cracks.
critic.name: Victor Stiff
publication.name: That Shelf

quote: [Joaquin] Phoenix creates a snake of a man with few to no redeeming qualities and along the way he turns in a blistering performance that should get him a front row seat on Oscar night.
critic.name: Dwight Brown
publication.name: National Newspaper Publishers Association

quote: Joaquin Phoenix is, far and above, the best part of Joker. Besides him, though, this is a comic book story dead on arrival.
critic.name: David Fontana
publication.name: Film Inquiry

quote: [Todd] Phillips and [Joaquin] Phoenix deserve credit for reimagining what a comic book movie can be. One that isn't encumbered with setting up multi-movie plot lines and one that can go to places other films in this genre can't.
critic.name: Mark Daniell
publication.name: Toronto Sun

quote: If Scorsese's 1976 classic Taxi Driver is a classier comparison for what Phillips concocts, what we have here is, without a doubt, a success thanks to an uncomfortable, disturbing portrait of a social outcast by Joaquin Phoenix.
critic.name: Nicholas Bell
publication.name: IONCINEMA.com

quote: There is a lot of exceptional work on display here, but I can't shake the fact that I felt kind of empty at the end of it.
critic.name: Perri Nemiroff
publication.name: Perri Nemiroff (YouTube)

quote: If nothing else, Todd Phillips's Joker proves that two scenes do not a movie make.
critic.name: Bill Chambers
publication.name: Film Freak Central

quote: A fascinating and portentous story in its size and psychological scope. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Diego Batlle
publication.name: Otroscines.com

quote: Fueled by strong performances and a disturbing story, "Joker" is one of the most interesting movies this year. Regardless of the reactions to it, it will be something that's going to talked about for a long time.
critic.name: Adriana Gomez-Weston
publication.name: AwardsCircuit.com

quote: Although "Joker," directed with passionate fury by Todd Phillips, is an entirely gripping movie, one cannot imagine it being as successful without Phoenix's landmark performance.
critic.name: Jordan Ruimy
publication.name: World of Reel

quote: This movie is indeed terrifying, but that's because it's horrifically, unintentionally insightful of how such men are viewed, both from without and within.
critic.name: Andrea Thompson
publication.name: The Young Folks

quote: This is a fascinating, occasionally charming movie about a clown with an artsy veneer.
critic.name: Sarah Hagi
publication.name: The Muse/Jezebel

quote: In Joker there's no finesse, no nuance between the delusion of one narcissist and the hypnosis of an infected society ready to burn itself to the ground in the name of power.
critic.name: Ella Kemp
publication.name: Culture Whisper

quote: Attention to detail and creativity combined with a bit of madness and a fully realized lead performance make Joker one of the most creative endeavors of the year.
critic.name: Dustin Chase
publication.name: Galveston Daily News

quote: There's a more audacious film lurking in "Joker," yet there's no denying how the discourse that'll soak up the airwaves is exactly the type of conversation the iconic villain would want us to have. Whether we like it or not, the joke's on us.
critic.name: Nate Adams
publication.name: The Only Critic

quote: When he finally does, Phillips builds to a climax of chaotic evil that certainly ranks among the most technically accomplished sequences of his career.
critic.name: Charles Bramesco
publication.name: Birth.Movies.Death.

quote: A divisive, turbulent, and maddening work, 'Joker' will either feel like a breath of fresh air or simply too much.
critic.name: Doug Jamieson
publication.name: The Jam Report

quote: Honestly, I'm not sure what Joker is here for, other than to cause a clumsily manufactured uproar.
critic.name: Barry Hertz
publication.name: Globe and Mail

quote: Joker is powerful and disturbing..in a good way. Phoenix has never been better AND scary. A highly entertaining drama that evolves to a can't forget thriller.
critic.name: Wilson Morales
publication.name: BlackFilm.com

quote: We can be content to enjoy a work that manages to modernize a character carved in the collective imagination in a completely original way. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Ruben Peralta Rigaud
publication.name: Cocalecas

quote: The movie isn't badly made or even ugly to look at, but there's a mean, smug little heart at the center of it that, at best, irresponsibly frames a familiar male power fantasy as a revolutionary act.
critic.name: Emma Stefansky
publication.name: Thrillist

quote: The most uncompromising American film since FIRST REFORMED.
critic.name: Chris Bumbray
publication.name: JoBlo's Movie Network

quote: There are many brilliant moments in the film, most of which are provided by Phoenix himself. But the dramatic intensity can be a lot to stand. You could almost hear Heath Ledger's Joker ask "Why so serious?" [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: María Fernanda Mugica
publication.name: Otroscines.com

quote: Joker is a dark and complex exploration of mental illness, led by Phoenix's phenomenal performance, which elevates the film to the next level.
critic.name: Scott Menzel
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: JOKER looks for human decency rather than anarchic wish fulfillment.
critic.name: James Clay
publication.name: Fresh Fiction

quote: There's plenty about Joker that makes it always compelling and watchable.
critic.name: Nick Johnston
publication.name: Vanyaland

quote: As Hannah Arendt saw banality in the supposed evil of the Nazi Adolf Eichmann, I see in Joker an attempt to elevate nerdy revenge to the plane of myth. That's scary on a lot of different levels.
critic.name: David Edelstein
publication.name: New York Magazine/Vulture

quote: Joker will truly change how we view comic book films and is one of the best origin films ever done. Joker is a truly disturbing and terrifying commentary on our current society. Joaquin Phoenix delivers a chilling performance that everyone will remember.
critic.name: Sharronda Williams
publication.name: Pay or Wait

quote: Todd Phillips' Joker offers a new take on The Clown Prince of Crime, one that unapologetically holds up a mirror in our divided modern times.
critic.name: Courtney Small
publication.name: Cinema Axis

quote: There's probably a lot of fanfiction out there that's far more innovative, provocative, profane, incisive, and effective than Joker.
critic.name: Sarah Kurchak
publication.name: Consequence

quote: Light on the laughs and lacking in moral backbone of its own, Joker settles for its decent performances and some stylish filmmaking
critic.name: Adam Solomons
publication.name: HeyUGuys

quote: It hardly matters if the audience is aware of the Joker's origin story or not because there is only one way that this tale can end. This, unfortunately, robs the film of most of its tension and rising action.
critic.name: Joe Lipsett
publication.name: Bloody Disgusting

quote: Despite Joaquin Phoenix's performance, this super-serious stand-alone origin story is very expensive and utterly hollow.
critic.name: Norman Wilner
publication.name: NOW Toronto

quote: Joker is a tightly directed mood piece with an unforgettable performance at its center, but it's not much more than a mask, with nothing but banality behind.
critic.name: Alissa Wilkinson
publication.name: Vox

quote: Joker may cop its values, aesthetic and philosophical, from other films, but at least it has values.
critic.name: A.A. Dowd
publication.name: AV Club

quote: Joker is no joke. The film challenges our emotions and prods at some fundamental ideas and biases. It's a complex tale told with sophistication and nuance, far quieter and more precise than the rhetoric will surely be.
critic.name: Jason Gorber
publication.name: HighDef Digest

quote: The film is one that might have been dreamed up by one of the cynical bros from the Hangover during a blacked-out stupor.
critic.name: Keith Uhlich
publication.name: Slant Magazine

quote: The Clown Prince of Crime has always been a favorite character to play for actors, but here Joaquin Phoenix takes it to its darkest place.
critic.name: Jason Guerrasio
publication.name: Business Insider

quote: A 'Taxi Driver' for the era of memes. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Luis Martínez
publication.name: El Mundo (Spain)

quote: Phoenix carries all the load in a movie that transcends the comic pages and will provoque all types of reactions. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Orlando Maldonado
publication.name: Movie Network

quote: Joker is the perfect movie for 2019. Joker is our comeuppance.
critic.name: Mike Ryan
publication.name: Uproxx

quote: It's a beautiful demented jewel of a film. The superhero movie, alas, for our time.
critic.name: Kevin Maher
publication.name: Times (UK)

quote: ...it's certainly worth seeing for Phoenix, whose mournful eyes and choking laugh perfectly embody his character's lifelong query: "Is it just me, or is it getting crazier out there?"
critic.name: Sara Stewart
publication.name: New York Post

quote: Todd Phillips directs violently bonkers, disturbing reimagined, reinvigorated version of one of DC Comics favorite villains with batshit, crazy , genius performance from Joaquin Phoenix. Also starring Zazie Beetz, Frances Conroy and Shea Whigham
critic.name: Carla Renata
publication.name: The Curvy Film Critic

quote: JOKER-a middlebrow impression of highbrow-has a moral compass, and it's pointed in the wrong direction.
critic.name: Rubin Safaya
publication.name: Cinemalogue

quote: Joker isn't the traditional comic book movie and presents villains sympathetically in a cringe-worthy way.
critic.name: Danielle Solzman
publication.name: Solzy at the Movies

quote: Joker is by no means an easy film to watch, but one that so ardently points out our shortcomings as a society. Incredibly poignant and disconcerting.
critic.name: Ashley Menzel
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: A violent, nihilistic horror film masquerading as both a character drama and a comic book movie
critic.name: Chris Evangelista
publication.name: Slashfilm

quote: This predictable brand of cold-hearted cynicism is not worth your time. Seriously.
critic.name: Mara Reinstein
publication.name: Us Weekly

quote: A movie with the message this one hammers home again and again... feels too volatile, and frankly too scary, to separate from the very real violence committed by young men like Joaquin Phoenix's Arthur Fleck in America almost every day.
critic.name: Leah Greenblatt
publication.name: Entertainment Weekly

quote: Joaquin Phoenix's phenomenal performance elevates this creepy, somber, and disturbing origin story that excels when it focuses on its titular character and stumbles when it tries to be a civics lesson
critic.name: J. Don Birnam
publication.name: Splash Report

quote: A macabre masterpiece, Joker's social relevance may be disputed for years, but the film and its star may never be denied the grandeur of their cinematic revolution.
critic.name: Luke Parker
publication.name: We Got This Covered

quote: Joker is more like a Scorsese film than a new DCEU installment, with its pitiful, lawless subject a 1981 blend of Rupert Pupkin, Travis Bickle, and Christine Chubbuck.
critic.name: Luke Hicks
publication.name: Film School Rejects

quote: They do not disguise their debt to Martin Scorsese in a film that has clear echoes of The King of Comedy and Taxi Driver, yet Joker is also thrillingly original, with an extraordinary performance by Phoenix at its dark heart.
critic.name: Kate Muir
publication.name: Daily Mail (UK)

quote: For the most part, it works a treat.
critic.name: Kaleem Aftab
publication.name: iNews.co.uk

quote: After a lot of throat-clearing, Joker finally becomes the movie it wants to be, positioning its protagonist squarely as the antagonist in the Batman mythos we know so well.
critic.name: Baradwaj Rangan
publication.name: Film Companion

quote: Todd Phillips' Joker is deeply unsettling. It's a film which follows you home at night, insidious and nightmarish
critic.name: Laura Potier
publication.name: Starburst

quote: There are a lot more details that comic book fans will pick up on, but ultimately what struck me the most about JOKER is that it's an ode to and a requiem for the little people.
critic.name: Zhuo-Ning Su
publication.name: Awards Daily

quote: Much of what shouldn't work are sold in entirety by Phoenix's performance; if Joker ultimately proves anything it's that he's the best actor of his generation.
critic.name: Jack King
publication.name: GQ Magazine [UK]

quote: The New Hollywood... [the] traumatized heir of the previous decades' great problems, finds a worthy successor in the visualizaion that [director Todd] Phillips recycles for his film. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Mariona Borrull
publication.name: El antepenúltimo mohicano

quote: However unusual its grungy 70s styling may be, Joker is ultimately nothing but a flimsy, two-hour supervillain origin movie...
critic.name: Nicholas Barber
publication.name: BBC.com

quote: Joker is a thunderously powerful character study of a man with a mental illness, and a ferocious indictment of a society that doesn't treat the mentally ill with the same compassion it shows to, say, cancer sufferers.
critic.name: Brian Viner
publication.name: Daily Mail (UK)

quote: It's nothing less (and nothing more) than an agent of unbridled chaos.
critic.name: David Ehrlich
publication.name: indieWire

quote: The film begins in a pretty dark place and it only gets more and more miserable as it goes on, with no relief in sight.
critic.name: Stephanie Watts
publication.name: SciFiNow

quote: Ideas-wise, it's only slightly less superficial than so many other comic-book movies, but judging by pure entertainment factor, it's a thrill to watch.
critic.name: Christina Newland
publication.name: Sight & Sound

quote: Phoenix and Phillips together have crafted something extraordinarily special. An exhilarating character study on the parameters of loneliness with a chilling assessment of the choking and deliberating effects of a morbid society.
critic.name: Jak-Luke Sharp
publication.name: Film Inquiry

quote: Creates its own world of dank, hopeless urban alienation and tells its own tale of class-based chaos and its newfound champion.
critic.name: Mark Keizer
publication.name: CineGods.com

quote: Like the best of the New Hollywood classics it references, this is a film that exhilarates and unsettles while having something to say about today.
critic.name: Raphael Abraham
publication.name: Financial Times

quote: Joker touches on the Batman mythology, although in some ways this is the least interesting aspect of the film - certainly when you've got Phoenix going full tilt.
critic.name: James Mottram
publication.name: South China Morning Post

quote: Phillips disenfranchises himself from the digital paraphernalia that predominates modern Hollywood. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Manu Yáñez
publication.name: Fotogramas

quote: Joker may not be a disaster, but it is also no masterpiece. It remains a highly controlled blockbuster made to facilitate the survival of the franchise and its marketing campaign. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Esther Miguel Trula
publication.name: Espinof

quote: Phoenix's committed performance is equal parts Freddie Quell, Joe from You Were Never Really Here, Fred Astaire, and Rupert Pupkin, all crossed-over intensity, flailing limbs, and physical comedy.
critic.name: Rory O'Connor
publication.name: The Film Stage

quote: "Joker" achieves two contradictory goals simultaneously, delivering a blockbuster that highlights what is eternally captivating about the character, while at the same time offering a sobering critique of the nihilism that has long been the Joker's M.O.
critic.name: Tim Grierson
publication.name: Screen International

quote: Joaquin Phoenix kills it in dark, timely DC origin movie that is no laughing matter. Will he be second Joker to win an Oscar?
critic.name: Pete Hammond
publication.name: Deadline Hollywood Daily

quote: This is a truly nightmarish vision of late-era capitalism - arguably the best social horror film since Get Out - and Joaquin Phoenix is magnetic in it.
critic.name: Philip De Semlyen
publication.name: Time Out

quote: If you strip the Joker and his nearly 80-year history as a cultural icon out of this film, as well as all the 1970s movie homages, there's not a whole lot left except for Phoenix's performance, and it's the kind of turn that's destined to be divisive.
critic.name: Alonso Duralde
publication.name: TheWrap

quote: This is the world post-Joker and with nothing but shaky-breathed respect for the filmmaking and storytelling achievement it represents, God help us all.
critic.name: Jessica Kiang
publication.name: The Playlist

quote: Todd Phillips delivered a game changing comic book film, and I cannot wait to see it again.
critic.name: Dorian Parks
publication.name: Geeks of Color

quote: It's chilling and ironically, still a fun way to spend two-hours escaping into a fictional world. Joker is such a great film that ventures away from the comic books and dives more into reality.
critic.name: Catalina Combs
publication.name: Black Girl Nerds

quote: Whether Joker is a social commentary on issues such as poverty or mental illness, a new mysterious take on the best known DC Comics villain, or another unforgettable piece of cinema by Martin Scorsese, you'll need to see to believe it.
critic.name: Brandon Davis
publication.name: ComicBook.com

quote: Joker is one of the true masterpieces of the superhero cinema, and one of 2019's greatest achievements.
critic.name: Mark Hughes
publication.name: Forbes

quote: Joker is a solid, well-made film that, ultimately, has a bit of an identity crisis.
critic.name: Germain Lussier
publication.name: io9.com

quote: Having brazenly plundered the films of Scorsese, Phillips fashions stolen ingredients into something new, so that what began as a gleeful cosplay session turns progressively more dangerous - and somehow more relevant, too.
critic.name: Xan Brooks
publication.name: Guardian

quote: Phoenix has plumbed depths so deep and given such a complex, brutal and physically transformative performance, it would be no surprise to see him take home a statuette or two come award season.
critic.name: John Bleasdale
publication.name: CineVue

quote: What do you get when you take a poor, mentally unstable loner and you treat him like trash? The answer given in Todd Phillips's ingenious new feature is Batman's arch nemesis, the Joker.
critic.name: Geoffrey Macnab
publication.name: Independent (UK)

quote: Joker succeeds thanks to the talents of Phoenix, who's crafted a layered, terror-inducing antagonist, and earned his rightful place alongside Heath Ledger and Jack Nicholson in the pantheon of all-time-great Jokers.
critic.name: Marlow Stern
publication.name: The Daily Beast

quote: Nobody who sees this new film will ever need any other version.
critic.name: David Sexton
publication.name: London Evening Standard

quote: Phillips may want us to think he's giving us a movie all about the emptiness of our culture, but really, he's just offering a prime example of it.
critic.name: Stephanie Zacharek
publication.name: TIME Magazine

quote: As social commentary, Joker is pernicious garbage.
critic.name: Glenn Kenny
publication.name: RogerEbert.com

quote: Feeble posturing, asinine pop psychology and political analysis charged with all the cynicism of a mollycoddled teen dropout in fake Oakleys and a home customised Linkin Park tee.
critic.name: David Jenkins
publication.name: Little White Lies

quote: Superhero blockbuster this is not: a playful fireman's-pole-based homage to the old Batman television series is one of a very few lighthearted moments in an otherwise oppressively downbeat and reality-grounded urban thriller...
critic.name: Robbie Collin
publication.name: Daily Telegraph (UK)

quote: Bold, devastating and utterly beautiful, Todd Phillips and Joaquin Phoenix have not just reimagined one of the most iconic villains in cinema history, but reimagined the comic book movie itself.
critic.name: Terri White
publication.name: Empire Magazine

quote: I've not always gotten along with Phoenix's mannered, muscle-strained approach to his craft, but here he makes a compelling case for going full-tilt.
critic.name: Richard Lawson
publication.name: Vanity Fair

quote: "Joker" is a dark, brooding and psychologically plausible origin story, a vision of cartoon sociopathy made flesh.
critic.name: Justin Chang
publication.name: Los Angeles Times

quote: Joaquin Phoenix's fully committed performance and Todd Phillips' masterful albeit loose reinvention of the DC source material make Joker a film that should leave comic book fans and non-fans alike disturbed and moved in all the right ways.
critic.name: Jim Vejvoda
publication.name: IGN Movies

quote: More character study than comic book movie, and anchored by an Oscar-worthy Joaquin Phoenix, Joker is a bravura blockbuster that proves you don't need superpowered scraps to dazzle.
critic.name: Jordan Farley
publication.name: Total Film

quote: Simply calling Joker a "comic book movie" does it a disservice; it is a story that feels like it could be about any number of disaffected people who are marginalized by the ruthless world in which we live.
critic.name: Dan Casey
publication.name: Nerdist

quote: A dazzlingly disturbed psycho morality play, one that speaks to the age of incels and mass shooters and no-hope politics, of the kind of hate that emerges from crushed dreams.
critic.name: Owen Gleiberman
publication.name: Variety

quote: "Joaquin Phoenix is astounding as Arthur Fleck/Joker...I think this is going to be a definitive part of Joker canon."
critic.name: Jenna Busch
publication.name: VitalThrills.com

quote: Joker is wild, crazy, and intense, and I was left speechless by the end of the film. Joaquin Phoenix delivers a spine-chilling performance. Todd Phillips has done to the Joker what Nolan has done to Batman with an origin story that feels very real.
critic.name: John Nguyen
publication.name: Nerd Reactor

quote: Not to discredit the imaginative vision of the writer-director, his co-scripter and invaluable tech and design teams, but Phoenix is the prime force that makes Joker such a distinctively edgy entry in the Hollywood comics industrial complex.
critic.name: David Rooney
publication.name: Hollywood Reporter

quote: You'll definitely feel like you'll need a shower after seeing it, but once you've dried off and changed clothes, you'll want to do nothing else but parse and dissect it.
critic.name: Eric Eisenberg
publication.name: CinemaBlend
